race.comment: UNDERRATED (2) is in the high-striking Clinton Taylor stable and was heavily bet when narrowly beaten here first-up from a wide gate. Maps better today and Butler replaces Wiggins. He's raced well in stronger than this and has placed 2/2 second-up. He's the one they have to beat.   RAVENITE (3) comes out of the same race and didn't have the best of it. He came from the back beaten a whisker the one before and impressed. Winning rider Cartwright is reunited, and he should be in the finish. LULO ROSE (6) did nothing dropping back to 800m at Twin Hills but went close here and at Townsville the two prior from the speed. Maps well today and can go better over the longer sprint. HOLY CROWN (8) was sharply better just missing at Rockhampton but has to manage an outside barrier.
